The paper deals with structured high-cardinality data and proposes algorithms for approximating the maximum-likelihood estimate of an unknown distribution conditioned on a known graphical model. This involves using sketches to estimate factors of the graphical model, which suggests a connection to algorithms for data streaming and sketching. Therefore, likely arXiv CS sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
